 you through 28 Arabic-language feature films. Written specially for students, the book is split into 3 parts: Egypt, North Africa and the eastern Arab world. Each part begins with an introductory essay that highlights the aesthetic and socio-historical trends and currents in the cinematic traditions particular to that region. Marlé Hammond then dedicates individual chapters to a group of films from the highlighted region, interpreting their form and content through the lenses of cinematic technique and concepts drawn from various disciplines in the arts, humanities and social sciences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion pictureszArab countriesxHistory and criticism. 0aMotion pictures, ArabxHistory and criticism. 4aIslamic Studies. 7aART / African.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079765740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147443579640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474435796423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474435796/original  a978-3-11-079765-7  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles